    <stitle>ANTILOCK MODULATOR ASSEMBLY: BENDIX M-21 AND M-22 - OPERATION - NON-ANTILOCK HOLD</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>NON-ANTILOCK HOLD</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0403004">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0403004" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0403004" filename="../figg04/G0403004.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Non-Antilock Hold</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>When the desired air pressure is attained in the service brake chambers, the brake system is in the
            Holding position. In the Holding position, both solenoids in the modulator remain de-energized and the
            balance of the internal components remain in the same position as they assumed during application.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
